text: Gonystylus nobilis is a species of plant in the family Thymelaeaceae. It is a tree endemic to Borneo where it is confined to Sarawak. The species has been assessed as Endangered on the IUCN Red List due to conversion of its forest habitat to palm oil plantations. ==References== nobilis Category:Endemic flora of Borneo Category:Trees of Borneo Category:Flora of Sarawak Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
